com.facebook.buck.rules

Class Repository.Builder

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.facebook.buck.rules.Repository.Builder
  • Enclosing class:
    Repository

    @NotThreadSafe
public static final class Repository.Builder
extends java.lang.Object
    Builds instances of Repository. Initialized attributes and then invoke build() method to create immutable instance.

    Builder is not thread safe and generally should not be stored in field or collection, but used immediately to create instances.

      • from

        public final Repository.Builder from(com.facebook.buck.rules.AbstractRepository instance)
        Adjust builder with values from provided AbstractRepository instance. Regular attribute values will be overridden, i.e. replaced with ones of an instance. Instance's absent optional values will not be copied (will not override current). Collection elements and entries will be added, not replaced.
        Parameters:
        instance - instance to copy values from
        Returns:
